The ternary operator should not be used
Why is this an issue? While the ternary operator is pleasingly compact, its use can make code more difficult to read. It should therefore be avoided in favor of the more verbose if/else structure. 
### Noncompliant
System.out.println(i>10?"yes":"no");
### Compliant
if (i > 10) {
  System.out.println(("yes");
} else {
  System.out.println("no");
}
### Noncompliant
{{BUGGY}}
### Compliant
